<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus inconspicuous, endolithic. Perithecia 0.15-0.25 mm, 3/4-1-immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock. Involucrellum absent. Exciple ca. 0.25-0.3 mm in diam., wall black. Periphysoids ca. 30-40 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm. Ascospores 0-septate, 17-23 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
11-12(-14) mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The species differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. devergens" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. foveolata" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="foveolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. foveolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species treated in the Taxonomy section in smaller spores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
